fwprop.note:
Start Action for (12,35) command which carries a list of Functional
Monitor (FMON) Identifiers whose definition is to be reported. 
The index i iterates over all functional monitors in the command but
the list of functional monitor identifiers may be empty.

fwprop.entryDesc:
Load invalid Functional
Monitor Identifier in the
data pool item verFailData

Run Command Verification
Failure Procedure to generate (1,4) 
report with failure code VER_ILL_MON

Set action outcome to 'failure'
with failure code VER_MON_ST_FD

fwprop.note:
This procedure generates a (1,4) report for each invalid FMON identifier in the command.
The (1,4) reports are generated by the Command Verification Failure Procedure.
The start action is declared successful as long as at least one valid FMON ID is found.

Flag_1: The i-th FMON Identifier in the Command
is within range and its slot in the FMDL is non-empty

fwprop.entryDesc:
Determine the number N of (12,26)
reports which are needed to report the 
functional monitors required by the command
and retrieve N OutComponents of type
(12,26) from the OutFactory

fwprop.note:
Flag_2:OutFactory fails to generate
all requested OutComponents
